<div class='panel'><h1>Open to all, free to use.</h1>
<h2>Terms of Use</h2>
<p>We're working on it.</p>
<h3>Conduct</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Failure to use the "#nsfw" tag when media attached to a message depicts material unsuitable for viewing by a Canadian youth audience (persons under 18 years of age), examples of which include:
    <ul>
      <li>nudity</li>
      <li>graphic violence</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
<h3>Content</h3>
<p>The following types of content are explicitly forbidden and will result in revocation of access to the service:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Sexual depictions of children and youth (persons under 18 years of age)</li>
  <li>Threats of violence</li>
  <li>Content illegal in Canada and/or the United States of America.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Federated instances</h3>
<p>Generally, follow their rules when visiting. Remote members will be expected to follow ours. For jurisdiction, start at the beginning.</p>
<h3>Network abuse</h3>
<p>Don't do it.</p>
